structured.title: Football match chat in the stands
structured.overview: Casual conversation among several people while watching a live football match. They react to goals, refereeing decisions (including potential red cards and penalties), substitutions, and tactics (pressing, injury breaks, becoming more defensive in the second half). They discuss players by name, league position and points gap, and hopes for additional goals. Intermixed are small side comments about food (chicken breasts, pizza, sausages), being cold, stairs in the stadium, and light joking, but there are no concrete future plans or commitments made.
